WEBVTT

00:00.768 --> 00:04.136
- ♪

00:04.138 --> 00:06.171
- Alright, all done, Ms. Leah.

00:06.173 --> 00:09.508
- Mm, thank you, Lindor.

00:09.510 --> 00:12.511
So, just like a
businessman will tell you,

00:12.513 --> 00:15.948
the best way to solve a problem
is to prevent the problem

00:15.950 --> 00:17.549
before it starts.

00:17.551 --> 00:20.019
- I wish Brown's mommy and daddy
had lived by the same motto.

00:20.021 --> 00:23.322
- [laughter]
- Efe, Efe, not now.

00:23.324 --> 00:25.524
I want us to take
this seriously.

00:25.526 --> 00:28.127
- I'm serious.
- [laughter]

00:28.129 --> 00:30.195
- Prevent the problem.

00:30.197 --> 00:32.865
By the time trouble starts,
it's often too late.

00:32.867 --> 00:34.366
- Hence, my point.

00:34.368 --> 00:36.702
Brown is now here and
we're stuck with him.

00:36.704 --> 00:38.070
- [laughter]

00:38.072 --> 00:40.072
- Nurse Leah, this is
wisdom, my lady.

00:40.074 --> 00:42.408
I only wish that some of
the folks in my courtroom

00:42.410 --> 00:44.143
could've understood
such simple facts.

00:44.145 --> 00:45.711
- Thank you, Judge Junie.

00:45.713 --> 00:48.280
The same principle
applies to your health.

00:48.282 --> 00:52.051
Preventive medicine is
about preventing diseases

00:52.053 --> 00:55.521
and other health problems
before they develop.

00:55.523 --> 00:58.590
- Ah, thank you
for setting up

00:58.592 --> 01:00.959
this health fair for
us, Nurse Leah.

01:00.961 --> 01:02.528
It is a blessing.

01:02.530 --> 01:06.432
In my country, healthcare's
not so readily available.

01:06.434 --> 01:08.133
- It's not always readily
available here either.

01:08.135 --> 01:09.468
- [doorbell]

01:09.470 --> 01:10.869
- Church service
was more drama

01:10.871 --> 01:13.772
than any of the Chitlin
Circuit theater I did.

01:13.774 --> 01:16.408
- Well, I didn't know
if we were, I didn't know

01:16.410 --> 01:18.610
if we was at church or
doing a reality show.

01:18.612 --> 01:21.980
I thought they was
gonna start fightin'

01:21.982 --> 01:23.916
- I am so sorry, Ms. Anastasia.

01:23.918 --> 01:25.818
I'm just, I'm just embarrassed.

01:25.820 --> 01:27.553
I cannot believe this.

01:27.555 --> 01:29.254
Hey Lindor, baby,
how you doing?

01:29.256 --> 01:31.557
- Hey Ms. Cora.
What happened in church?

01:31.559 --> 01:34.159
- The pastor's wife told
the whole congregation

01:34.161 --> 01:37.629
that her husband, the pastor,
had been sowing his wild oats

01:37.631 --> 01:40.232
with two women among
the congregation.

01:40.234 --> 01:42.000
- Sowing oats?

01:42.002 --> 01:44.002
What is that?
- [laughter]

01:44.004 --> 01:46.271
- You, you don't get it?

01:46.273 --> 01:47.639
The pastor was a rolling stone.
- [laughter]

01:47.641 --> 01:50.576
- Mr. Brown.
- What's a rolling stone?

01:50.578 --> 01:54.179
- He was doing love, boy.
- Oh.

01:54.181 --> 01:56.048
- MR. BROWN: You
young people.

01:56.050 --> 01:57.749
- The pastor's a playa.

01:57.751 --> 01:59.952
- It's not funny, sweetheart.
That's not funny.

01:59.954 --> 02:01.553
- My bad, I'm sorry.

02:01.555 --> 02:03.655
- Oh yes, Lindor, when
you finish all that mopping,

02:03.657 --> 02:05.624
can you go outside
and grab all that mail

02:05.626 --> 02:07.259
that's stuffed in
that mailbox, please?

02:07.261 --> 02:08.927
- Yes, ma'am.

02:08.929 --> 02:12.731
- Far be it for me to judge but
your pastor's just ridiculous.

02:12.733 --> 02:15.434
I mean, I'm not above
having a side piece,

02:15.436 --> 02:17.636
but I would never
stoop to his level.

02:17.638 --> 02:21.573
I mean, I had my husband and
my boyfriend, but that's it.

02:21.575 --> 02:24.843
Anything more would be
just disrespectful.

02:24.845 --> 02:27.980
- I'm so disappointed.
I can not believe Pastor.

02:27.982 --> 02:30.616
And I enjoy his sermons so.

02:30.618 --> 02:33.752
And now we gotta go
find a new church home.

02:33.754 --> 02:37.322
- Well, if he's a good
pastor, why leave?

02:37.324 --> 02:41.260
- Me and Cora don't play
all of that foolishness.

02:41.262 --> 02:43.362
We don't do all of that.

02:43.364 --> 02:45.230
And besides,
this is grown folk talk.

02:45.232 --> 02:47.299
- That's right.

02:47.301 --> 02:50.869
- Cora, I am so sorry you're
pastor disappointed you.

02:50.871 --> 02:55.674
Um, I'm gonna go check
out Leah's health fair.

02:55.676 --> 03:00.679
This is absolutely fabulous,
Leah.

03:00.681 --> 03:03.715
Oh, Marilyn would be
so proud of us.

03:03.717 --> 03:04.950
God rest her soul.

03:04.952 --> 03:06.285
- Yes, ma'am.

03:06.287 --> 03:08.187
She inspired this.

03:08.189 --> 03:10.489
We have to take care
of our bodies.

03:10.491 --> 03:12.324
- Hey Judge Junie, I
got some mail for you.

03:12.326 --> 03:15.360
- For me? I haven't
given anyone this address.

03:15.362 --> 03:17.863
- Didn't you write your son?

03:17.865 --> 03:19.398
- Oh, yes.

03:19.400 --> 03:22.434
Yes, yes, uh, he must have
written back, I'll take it.

03:26.807 --> 03:28.106
[laughs]

03:28.108 --> 03:30.175
This is the best
day of my life.

03:30.177 --> 03:31.510
- I'm so happy for
you, Reginald.

03:31.512 --> 03:33.045
- Life is so good.

03:38.819 --> 03:40.586
- ♪

03:40.588 --> 03:43.021
- ♪ No matter what you do,
I love you ♪

03:43.023 --> 03:47.059
♪ No matter where you go,
I'm behind you for sure ♪

03:47.061 --> 03:48.594
♪ Always remember ♪

03:48.596 --> 03:49.828
♪ Blood ain't never water ♪

03:49.830 --> 03:52.531
♪ We'll make it if
we stay together ♪

03:54.368 --> 03:55.534
- Alright, you ready
for your flu shot?

03:55.536 --> 03:57.669
- No.
- [laughter]

03:57.671 --> 04:00.572
- Anybody ever be
ready for a shot?

04:00.574 --> 04:02.441
- Okay, I just need
you to calm down.

04:02.443 --> 04:05.877
This is alcohol.
Alright. Okay.

04:05.879 --> 04:08.480
Can you be still? Be still.
Okay, good job.

04:08.482 --> 04:09.681
- Wait!
- [laughter]

04:09.683 --> 04:13.919
- Oh, good job, Mr. Brown.

04:13.921 --> 04:15.520
Moving along here.

04:15.522 --> 04:17.589
- Where you go?
Don't disappear.

04:17.591 --> 04:19.024
- I'm just getting
the needle ready.

04:19.026 --> 04:21.426
- Okay, make sure you
give me the right stuff.

04:21.428 --> 04:23.362
Don't give me nothing
to be growing extra hairs

04:23.364 --> 04:25.130
and legs and stuff.

04:25.132 --> 04:27.165
- Are you relaxed?
- I-I'm relaxed.

04:27.167 --> 04:28.834
- Relax your arm.
- Okay.

04:28.836 --> 04:32.938
- [audience laughter]
- Wait, wait, wait, wait, wait!

04:32.940 --> 04:35.107
- You need to breathe,
relax, so we can get this done.

04:35.109 --> 04:37.542
- Well, you ain't got to
rush me, acting like a--

04:37.544 --> 04:39.878
- Man, stop acting like a baby.
- Wait, what?

04:39.880 --> 04:42.781
This is A and B.
Why don't you see your way out?

04:42.783 --> 04:45.884
All up in here in our ice cream
and know what flavor it is.

04:45.886 --> 04:48.420
- Oh, what's the flavor,
scaredy cats?

04:48.422 --> 04:50.656
- Ain't nobody no scaredy cat.

04:50.658 --> 04:52.624
- Okay, will you two cut it out?
Cut it out.

04:52.626 --> 04:54.426
- Okay, I'm gonna ask
you this question.

04:54.428 --> 04:55.794
- Uh-huh. Alright.
- You better answer.

04:55.796 --> 04:57.796
- You promise to tell the truth,
the whole truth, and

04:57.798 --> 04:59.364
nothing but the truth?
- Yes.

04:59.366 --> 05:04.002
- Do you know what you doing?
- Yes. I'm a nurse, Mr. Brown.

05:04.004 --> 05:06.371
- Just 'cause you a nurse,
that don't mean you know

05:06.373 --> 05:08.674
what you doin'.
- [audience laughter]

05:08.676 --> 05:11.610
- You know if you get a bubble
in that thing you can kill me.

05:11.612 --> 05:13.645
- You won't die. Trust me.
- You sure?

05:13.647 --> 05:17.449
- Look at Cora. What she doin'?
- Cora, what--aagghh!

05:17.451 --> 05:19.017
- See, that wasn't so bad.

05:19.019 --> 05:20.585
- [audience laughter]

05:20.587 --> 05:24.756
- Aagghh!
- Mr. Brown.

05:24.758 --> 05:26.992
- What'd you do, stab me?
- [audience laughter]

05:26.994 --> 05:29.928
- You tricked me.
- I did not trick you.

05:29.930 --> 05:31.863
- You did trick me.
- [audience laughter]

05:31.865 --> 05:34.232
- You did great. See, now you
gonna be better prepared

05:34.234 --> 05:35.767
for the bug that's
out there.

05:35.769 --> 05:37.569
I heard it was pretty
bad this year.

05:37.571 --> 05:40.372
- You a lying nurse.
- [audience laughter]

05:40.374 --> 05:45.911
- Woo, look at you two.
Where you off to?

05:45.913 --> 05:48.480
- We're headed to get
Reginald an outfit.

05:48.482 --> 05:49.815
- What's the occasion?

05:49.817 --> 05:52.517
- Well, after 10 years
of not speaking,

05:52.519 --> 05:57.055
I'm having dinner
with my son.

05:57.057 --> 05:58.590
- Wow.

05:58.592 --> 06:00.459
Have fun.
- Mmhmm.

06:00.461 --> 06:02.494
- Okay.
- Ain't no okay.

06:02.496 --> 06:04.029
Naw, I ain't upset.

06:04.031 --> 06:05.530
I can't feel my legs.

06:05.532 --> 06:07.766
- Oh, Mr. Brown, go get
a snack out the kitchen.

06:07.768 --> 06:09.668
- You need to give
Efe one in the butt.

06:09.670 --> 06:11.603
- [laughter]
- You're next, Efe.

06:14.675 --> 06:16.808
- How was the concert, Son?

06:16.810 --> 06:18.510
- It was incredible, Dad.

06:18.512 --> 06:20.812
They brought out Drake
and Travis Scott.

06:20.814 --> 06:23.081
Straight up.
- [audience laughter]

06:23.083 --> 06:24.916
- How was Migos?

06:24.918 --> 06:27.853
- Lit. Momma!
- [audience laughter]

06:27.855 --> 06:30.222
- Hey Mom, did you send my
blue jacket to the cleaners?

06:30.224 --> 06:32.391
- Uh, no.

06:32.393 --> 06:33.825
- Um, I-I gotta go.

06:33.827 --> 06:35.894
I got a chemistry lab today.
- Okay.

06:35.896 --> 06:38.029
- You're not gonna
finish your breakfast?

06:38.031 --> 06:40.365
- Uh, I'm full.
Thanks Mom. Bye, Dad.

06:40.367 --> 06:41.867
- W-well, h-have
a good day!

06:41.869 --> 06:43.802
You, you not gonna
wait on your sister?

06:43.804 --> 06:45.670
- [door bell]
- Mom, I can't find it anywhere.

06:45.672 --> 06:47.739
- Oh, oh, did you
check your closet?

06:47.741 --> 06:49.174
- It's not there.
- [door bell]

06:49.176 --> 06:51.209
- Are you sure you didn't
put it down somewhere?

06:51.211 --> 06:53.445
Check the hall closet.

06:53.447 --> 06:55.814
- Hey, good morning.
Something smells good.

06:55.816 --> 06:57.883
- I was just making
breakfast for the kids.

06:57.885 --> 06:59.584
- Oh, you made breakfast?
- [audience laughter]

06:59.586 --> 07:01.052
- Yeah, you want something?

07:01.054 --> 07:03.221
- Oh no, I don't want anything.
Oatmeal too runny, mm-mm.

07:03.223 --> 07:05.624
- [audience laughter]

07:05.626 --> 07:08.226
- Hey.
- Yes, you made breakfast.

07:08.228 --> 07:10.529
That's alright.
- I did. You, you feeling okay?

07:10.531 --> 07:12.097
- I'm, you know, I'm feeling--

07:12.099 --> 07:14.833
I'm a little upset about what's
going on down at the church.

07:14.835 --> 07:17.035
It's got my nerves bad.
- I heard about the way

07:17.037 --> 07:18.703
they was carrying on
down there yesterday.

07:18.705 --> 07:20.939
- Yeah, I mean it's awful.
Terrible.

07:20.941 --> 07:22.841
- Yeah, that's too bad.
I know you really

07:22.843 --> 07:24.209
liked that pastor, too.
- Yes.

07:24.211 --> 07:26.778
I don't know no other pastor
that can preach like him.

07:26.780 --> 07:29.481
That man can really preach.
I hate that.

07:29.483 --> 07:31.216
- That's a shame, Cora.
- Yes, it is.

07:31.218 --> 07:32.651
- I mean, a shame.
- It is.

07:32.653 --> 07:34.786
Now, the whole city is
talking about us.

07:34.788 --> 07:36.388
It's just heartbreaking.

07:36.390 --> 07:38.557
Just for the whole
body of Christ.

07:38.559 --> 07:40.792
- Mm, that's just a shame.

07:46.183 --> 07:47.682
- Alright, now you do this one.

07:47.684 --> 07:49.317
What are the reactants?

07:49.319 --> 07:53.388
- Heck if I know!
- [audience laughter]

07:53.390 --> 07:55.891
- Stop playing, get serious.

07:55.893 --> 07:59.027
- Um, hydrogen...

07:59.029 --> 08:02.197
and what's that, chlorine?

08:02.199 --> 08:05.467
- Good.
But how much of each?

08:05.469 --> 08:07.502
- [audience laughter]

08:07.504 --> 08:09.471
- Man, I don't know.
A little? Hey!

08:09.473 --> 08:11.439
- [audience laughter]

08:11.441 --> 08:14.576
- Okay.

08:14.578 --> 08:18.079
Uh, two parts hydrogen

08:18.081 --> 08:21.349
and two parts chlorine.

08:21.351 --> 08:23.518
- Right.
Those are the reactants.

08:23.520 --> 08:26.521
So, what is the product?

08:26.523 --> 08:29.324
- Uh, HCL--
- [door bell]

08:29.326 --> 08:31.726
- Hydrogen chloride.
- Good.

08:31.728 --> 08:34.262
What's going on, Lindor?
- What's up, Mr. Washington?

08:34.264 --> 08:35.564
- What's up, Philip,
you ready?

08:35.566 --> 08:37.832
- Almost.
- Oh, y'all going downtown.

08:37.834 --> 08:41.169
Look, make sure you
have him back in two hours.

08:41.171 --> 08:43.772
- What are you guys doing?
- Chemistry homework.

08:43.774 --> 08:46.341
- Who do you have?
- Mr. Quinn.

08:46.343 --> 08:48.076
- Oh, bro, he's the worst.

08:48.078 --> 08:49.945
- [audience laughter]

08:49.947 --> 08:51.546
- Young people make
sure your--

08:51.548 --> 08:54.382
- BOTH: Reactants
are in the formula.

08:54.384 --> 08:56.184
- [audience laughter]

08:56.186 --> 08:58.920
- Hey, man, you did a
good job out in the yard today.

08:58.922 --> 09:01.489
- Thanks.
- Yeah, keep up the good work.

09:01.491 --> 09:03.525
- Hey, you know where
Judge Junie's headed?

09:03.527 --> 09:05.760
He's looking like
new money out there.

09:05.762 --> 09:07.662
- Oh, yeah, um,
he's actually going

09:07.664 --> 09:09.097
to meet with
his son today.

09:09.099 --> 09:11.533
He hasn't seen him in,
like, ten years or something.

09:11.535 --> 09:15.670
- Wow, good for him.
- Yeah.

09:15.672 --> 09:18.273
- You are such a disease!
- [audience laughter]

09:18.275 --> 09:20.141
- Well, hello to you, too.
- [audience laughter]

09:20.143 --> 09:22.577
- You're dishonest and
you're a thief.

09:22.579 --> 09:24.446
- Dang girl, what I do?

09:24.448 --> 09:27.282
- What's going on?
- Dad, look at this.

09:27.284 --> 09:29.417
- Oh.
- [audience laughter]

09:29.419 --> 09:33.121
- Yeah, I'm just gonna
study, uh, alone.

09:33.123 --> 09:34.823
- [audience laughter]

09:34.825 --> 09:37.259
- Pump your brakes.
You're not going nowhere.

09:37.261 --> 09:39.494
- All this time I've been
looking for my jacket,

09:39.496 --> 09:41.463
and look at this picture
I just saw online.

09:41.465 --> 09:43.064
Philip took my jacket
to the Migos concert

09:43.066 --> 09:45.500
without my permission.
- Wait, I made it online?

09:45.502 --> 09:47.636
- [audience laughter]

09:47.638 --> 09:49.838
- Philip, why did you do that?

09:49.840 --> 09:51.806
- I'm not gonna lie, Dad.

09:51.808 --> 09:54.175
The jacket just went
really well with my outfit.

09:54.177 --> 09:55.577
- [audience laughter]
- Yeah, give me my

09:55.579 --> 09:57.045
jacket, Philip.

09:57.047 --> 10:00.515
- I-I wish I could,
but I lost it.

10:00.517 --> 10:01.883
- You lost my jacket?

10:01.885 --> 10:04.986
- Hey look, I didn't mean to.
I'm sorry.

10:04.988 --> 10:08.123
- What did I tell you
about losing things?

10:08.125 --> 10:10.659
And how do you lose a jacket
that you're wearing?

10:10.661 --> 10:12.494
- Alright, look,
it's not my fault.

10:12.496 --> 10:14.129
So, I'm at the concert, right?

10:14.131 --> 10:16.331
And then they start
playing "Walk It Talk It".

10:16.333 --> 10:18.700
And I'm feeling it, right?

10:18.702 --> 10:20.969
- [audience laughter]
- Right, right, right.

10:20.971 --> 10:22.871
And then, and then,
I'm getting a little hot.

10:22.873 --> 10:24.172
So, I take the jacket off.

10:24.174 --> 10:26.207
Then, they start playing
"Bad and Bougie".

10:26.209 --> 10:30.045
Now, I'm really in the zone.
- [audience laughter]

10:30.047 --> 10:32.914
- Okay, okay and the next thing
you know, the jacket's gone.

10:32.916 --> 10:35.550
- Dad, you have to
do something.

10:35.552 --> 10:36.951
- So, why didn't you
say something?

10:36.953 --> 10:39.521
- I was gonna go online
to replace it.

10:39.523 --> 10:42.457
But look at this,
it's one of a kind.

10:42.459 --> 10:44.292
Special edition.
Who, who woulda knew?

10:44.294 --> 10:45.694
- [audience laughter]

10:45.696 --> 10:47.662
- Only one is in the world
and she got it.

10:47.664 --> 10:50.098
How?
Look, look, I'm sorry.

10:50.100 --> 10:52.233
- I will never forgive
you for this.

10:52.235 --> 10:54.769
You guys let him get
away with everything.

10:54.771 --> 10:56.871
- Come on, Sandra,
wait a minute.

10:56.873 --> 10:58.139
- A little dramatic.
- [audience laughter]

10:58.141 --> 11:00.308
- It's a danim jacket,
a denim jacket.

11:05.582 --> 11:07.782
- Wow.
- [audience laughter]

11:07.784 --> 11:11.119
- Right? I mean,
and you wanna date that.

11:11.121 --> 11:12.754
- [audience laughter]
- I think you should make

11:12.756 --> 11:15.256
up with your sister. It'll
make it a lot easier on me.

11:15.258 --> 11:16.624
- [audience laughter]

11:16.626 --> 11:21.896
- Eh, look, I know my sister.

11:21.898 --> 11:25.734
She's just gonna be mad
for the rest of the century.

11:25.736 --> 11:27.802
Good luck.
- [audience laughter]

11:27.804 --> 11:29.137
- Alright, man, well,
just hurry up.

11:29.139 --> 11:31.072
We gotta go downtown.
- Alright.

11:31.074 --> 11:32.273
- [door bell]

11:35.145 --> 11:36.978
- Hey Judge Junie.

11:36.980 --> 11:38.947
You looking sharp in
that outfit, man.

11:38.949 --> 11:40.915
- Too bad I can't
take it back.

11:40.917 --> 11:44.285
- I heard you were meeting
up with your son, right?

11:44.287 --> 11:46.588
- You heard wrong.

11:46.590 --> 11:48.890
- Is everything okay?
- He stood me up.

11:48.892 --> 11:52.360
- What, he didn't come?

11:52.362 --> 11:55.864
- No, my son hates me.

11:59.970 --> 12:01.469
- ♪
- Don't say that Judge.

12:01.471 --> 12:03.605
I'm sure your son
doesn't hate you.

12:03.607 --> 12:06.808
- Oh, he does.
- Why do say that?

12:06.810 --> 12:09.043
- When I divorced his mother...

12:09.045 --> 12:14.315
- You divorced him too.
- No, I was always present.

12:14.317 --> 12:18.286
- Were you like my dad,
mean and strict?

12:18.288 --> 12:23.324
- I was a firm disciplinarian,
yes, but nothing Draconian.

12:25.729 --> 12:29.731
- I'm sorry, what?

12:29.733 --> 12:32.300
- You young people oughta
read something sometimes.

12:32.302 --> 12:34.903
I didn't go overboard.

12:34.905 --> 12:39.941
Uh, like I heard your dad did.

