- Okay, so then
what happened?

12:41.678 --> 12:44.345
- College happened.
- College?

12:44.347 --> 12:48.883
- He got so radical
and down for the cause

12:48.885 --> 12:51.686
and we would argue.

12:51.688 --> 12:55.056
At first, I thought it
was healthy debate.

12:55.058 --> 12:58.693
But it became more
bitter and resentful.

12:58.695 --> 13:01.930
- What were you guys
arguing about?

13:01.932 --> 13:05.200
- He didn't like
the judicial system.

13:05.202 --> 13:08.369
And his dad was part
of the judicial system.

13:08.371 --> 13:10.638
- Huh, my dad too.

13:10.640 --> 13:13.208
He's a, he's a sheriff.

13:13.210 --> 13:16.377
- Yeah, he likes to
dance, too, I heard.

13:16.379 --> 13:17.812
- [audience laughter]

13:17.814 --> 13:20.949
- Yeah, word gets around
pretty fast around here.

13:20.951 --> 13:23.351
- I don't want to bore you.
I'm sure you've got

13:23.353 --> 13:25.420
some place to be.
- You're not, you're not

13:25.422 --> 13:27.689
boring me at all.
I'm just waiting on Philip

13:27.691 --> 13:28.990
to go downtown.
- Hmm.

13:28.992 --> 13:30.625
- Plus I like talking
to old people.

13:30.627 --> 13:31.993
- [audience laughter]

13:31.995 --> 13:34.262
- But no, I meant I
really I think, um,

13:34.264 --> 13:36.865
more young guys like us need
wisdom from your generation.

13:36.867 --> 13:38.633
- Yeah.
- So, your son didn't like the

13:38.635 --> 13:41.669
fact that you were a judge?

13:41.671 --> 13:43.838
- Well, he did not.

13:43.840 --> 13:46.441
But I, on the other hand,

13:46.443 --> 13:48.576
was proud that I got criminals
off the street.

13:48.578 --> 13:53.114
I-I took pride in helping
make our streets safer.

13:53.116 --> 13:55.049
- Safer?
What, you didn't lock up a

13:55.051 --> 13:57.051
bunch of our brothers did you?
- I did.

13:57.053 --> 13:59.554
I-I locked up anyone
who committed a crime

13:59.556 --> 14:01.122
and I was very
proud of that.

14:01.124 --> 14:02.490
- The system throws
us black men away

14:02.492 --> 14:05.159
like our lives don't matter
and you were part of that?

14:05.161 --> 14:07.996
- Oh, no, you are starting
to sound just like my son.

14:07.998 --> 14:09.430
- But Judge, it's the truth.

14:09.432 --> 14:11.032
Alright, black men in
the judicial system--

14:11.034 --> 14:13.001
- Should make sure they
stay away from there

14:13.003 --> 14:17.772
if they really believed
their lives mattered.

14:17.774 --> 14:23.778
- Speaking of, Philip and I are
on our way to a peaceful vigil.

14:23.780 --> 14:26.948
- You are just like my son.

14:26.950 --> 14:28.349
- Uh, you ready?

14:28.351 --> 14:30.618
Um, my dad said I gotta
be back in two hours.

14:30.620 --> 14:35.490
- Goodnight, gentlemen.
Please, stay safe out there.

14:35.492 --> 14:37.392
- Yeah, goodnight, Judge.

14:40.730 --> 14:44.032
I'll be praying for you and
your son to patch things up.

14:44.034 --> 14:49.837
- Oh, that prayer has gone
unanswered for over ten years.

14:49.839 --> 14:52.206
- Sorry.

14:52.208 --> 14:54.576
- [knock at door]
- Knock, knock, knock.

14:54.578 --> 14:55.977
- Come in.

14:55.979 --> 14:57.345
- I found these clothes
in the laundry.

14:57.347 --> 14:59.147
- Oh, thank you.
I was just about to

14:59.149 --> 15:01.082
go grab them.
- Well, I figured since

15:01.084 --> 15:03.318
I was down there,
I'd just save you a trip.

15:03.320 --> 15:04.819
- Bless yo' heart
'cause you know

15:04.821 --> 15:06.287
those stairs can
take you out.

15:06.289 --> 15:10.425
- [laughter]
- You telling me.

15:10.427 --> 15:15.163
- I heard your pastor made
a public apology today.

15:15.165 --> 15:18.866
- Yeah, I heard, but I ain't
thinking about that man.

15:18.868 --> 15:20.368
- Mom.

15:20.370 --> 15:22.437
- Uh, honey, you see
Ms. Cora and I talking?

15:22.439 --> 15:24.772
- Sorry, Ms. Cora.
Mom, I need my own room.

15:24.774 --> 15:27.575
- I-I-I know you're father
and I have talked about it.

15:27.577 --> 15:30.211
Uh, y'all are too old to be
staying in the room together.

15:30.213 --> 15:32.146
- Mom, please.
I can't stay in there with him.

15:32.148 --> 15:33.715
- Well, what happened?

15:33.717 --> 15:35.650
- He stole my jacket
and then lost it.

15:35.652 --> 15:37.852
- Well, your dad told me.

15:37.854 --> 15:39.721
- I'm never talking
to him again.

15:39.723 --> 15:41.889
- Now, wait a minute,
now, hold on.

15:41.891 --> 15:43.191
He is your brother.

15:43.193 --> 15:45.259
You can't just stop
talking to him forever.

15:45.261 --> 15:46.694
- He's not my brother
anymore.

15:46.696 --> 15:49.297
- Well, did he apologize?
- Yes, but he should've

15:49.299 --> 15:51.866
never touched my stuff
without asking me.

15:51.868 --> 15:53.701
- Well, you have
a point there.

15:53.703 --> 15:55.637
That's true, but
he's your brother.

15:55.639 --> 15:56.871
And sometimes
family members

15:56.873 --> 15:58.640
do things that
we don't like

15:58.642 --> 16:00.541
but family is
all we have.

16:00.543 --> 16:02.610
- Mmhmm, Cora's right.

16:02.612 --> 16:05.113
That's your only brother
and you know how he is.

16:05.115 --> 16:06.447
- And that's not the point.

16:06.449 --> 16:08.716
He can't keep taking
my stuff without asking me.

16:08.718 --> 16:11.052
It's unforgivable.

16:11.054 --> 16:13.087
- Oh, that girl has to,
she gotta calm down.

16:13.089 --> 16:14.989
She's just, she just have to.

16:14.991 --> 16:17.725
- She will.
- Well, you know what?

16:17.727 --> 16:20.428
You gotta learn to forgive
people when they apologize.

16:20.430 --> 16:23.297
- Does that go for
your pastor too, Cora?

16:30.907 --> 16:33.007
- There you are.

16:33.009 --> 16:35.309
By all the bacon
in the refrigerator,

16:35.311 --> 16:38.212
I see you're back
to eating meat.

16:38.214 --> 16:41.416
- I just can't leave it alone.
I can't let that bacon go.

16:41.418 --> 16:43.551
I-I been praying.

16:43.553 --> 16:45.553
- About what?
- Bacon.

16:45.555 --> 16:47.522
- [audience laughter]

16:47.524 --> 16:49.924
- You've been praying
about bacon?

16:49.926 --> 16:51.759
- I been praying,
I been praying

16:51.761 --> 16:55.296
that I can get all the nutrients
that I need from bacon.

16:55.298 --> 16:56.631
Bacon, bacon, bacon.
- [audience laughter]

16:56.633 --> 16:59.967
- So, all the, what
the wellness, the health fair,

16:59.969 --> 17:03.604
everything about eating healthy,
it doesn't mean anything to you?

17:03.606 --> 17:06.174
- I just can't give up the pig.
The pig is my friend.

17:06.176 --> 17:08.943
- Yeah? Go, sit down.

17:08.945 --> 17:10.478
- What, what you--
- Sit down, my friend.

17:10.480 --> 17:12.513
- Well, you ain't got
to be so aggressive.

17:12.515 --> 17:15.116
You just, y'all--why y'all
tone is always sit down?

17:15.118 --> 17:16.617
- [audience laughter]
- Like you like Arnold

17:16.619 --> 17:17.919
Schwarzenegger.
- Shh.

17:17.921 --> 17:20.088
- Sit down now!
- Try this.

17:20.090 --> 17:21.622
- What is that?

17:21.624 --> 17:23.024
- Try it now.

17:27.597 --> 17:29.397
- Mmm.
- Mmm.

17:29.399 --> 17:32.333
- That's Jambalaya.
- Yes.

17:32.335 --> 17:36.304
- Yeah, I recognize that.
That's good Jambalaya.

17:36.306 --> 17:38.906
I like Jambalaya.
- And me too.

17:38.908 --> 17:40.608
- You made this?
- Yes.

17:40.610 --> 17:42.443
- See, I told you, pig.

17:42.445 --> 17:46.514
That makes stuff
taste better, the pig.

17:46.516 --> 17:49.050
- No meat.

17:49.052 --> 17:52.019
- You a lie.
That's sausage.

17:52.021 --> 17:54.889
- I liked Ms. Leah's talk
about preventive health.

17:54.891 --> 17:56.224
We have to keep eating healthy.

17:56.226 --> 17:58.493
We only have one body, yo.

17:58.495 --> 18:00.428
- Well, meat does
my body good.

18:00.430 --> 18:02.130
- [audience laughter]
- Look at this meat body.

18:02.132 --> 18:04.165
- [audience laughter]

18:04.167 --> 18:06.701
- Huh, damn.

18:06.703 --> 18:09.303
You should never eat
meat in this life or the next.

18:09.305 --> 18:11.205
- [audience laughter]
- [door bell]

18:11.207 --> 18:13.441
- Mom, Dad.
Mom.

18:13.443 --> 18:15.109
Mr. Brown, where,
where is my dad?

18:15.111 --> 18:16.544
- In the back somewhere.
What?

18:16.546 --> 18:17.945
- What's wrong?

18:17.947 --> 18:19.413
- The, the police are
chasing us man.

18:19.415 --> 18:21.149
- For what?
- W-w-w-we were

18:21.151 --> 18:22.984
at a peaceful protest
and when we were

18:22.986 --> 18:24.452
leaving, the cops
just started following us.

18:24.454 --> 18:26.087
- What's wrong?
- Dad, Dad, the police

18:26.089 --> 18:27.455
were following us.

18:27.457 --> 18:28.923
- They were following,
for what?

18:28.925 --> 18:30.324
- Everything okay?
- No.

18:30.326 --> 18:32.727
- Dad, I'm scared.
- Calm, calm down, Son.

18:32.729 --> 18:35.029
It's okay, alright.
I'm not gonna let nothing

18:35.031 --> 18:36.564
happen to you alright.
- What's wrong?

18:36.566 --> 18:38.266
- The police followed Lindor
and Philip home.

18:38.268 --> 18:41.369
He's a little shaken up.
- Baby, are you okay?

18:44.040 --> 18:46.307
- So, wha-wha-what
were y'all doing?

18:46.309 --> 18:47.875
- We were at a
candlelight vigil

18:47.877 --> 18:49.210
and when we
were leaving

18:49.212 --> 18:50.611
the police just
started following us.

18:50.613 --> 18:52.246
- Well, if you weren't
doing anything,

18:52.248 --> 18:53.648
you have nothing
to worry about.

18:53.650 --> 18:56.784
- What planet do you live on?
- Mars.

18:56.786 --> 18:58.452
- [knocking]

18:58.454 --> 19:02.023
- How you know?
You don't even know what--

19:02.025 --> 19:05.159
- Jeremy, it's the police.

19:05.161 --> 19:08.529
- I see 'em baby.
Just calm down alright.

19:08.531 --> 19:10.164
Open the door.

19:17.140 --> 19:19.173
- Officers.

19:24.013 --> 19:25.680
- We're looking for
Lindor Luckett.

19:28.051 --> 19:30.051
We need you to
come with us, son.

19:30.053 --> 19:31.652
- ♪

19:36.809 --> 19:38.609
- We need you to
come with us, son.

19:38.611 --> 19:41.145
- I ain't your son.
Don't call me your son, bruh.

19:41.147 --> 19:42.747
- Just be quiet.
Calm down, baby, calm down.

19:42.749 --> 19:47.184
- Don't make it worse.
Don't make it worse.

19:47.186 --> 19:49.186
- Listen, Officer, my name
is Jeremy Washington

19:49.188 --> 19:52.056
and I live here.
Now, Lindor, he works for us.

19:52.058 --> 19:53.591
What is this about?

19:53.593 --> 19:55.860
- We have reason to believe
he was involved in a brutal

19:55.862 --> 19:57.194
assault today.
- Assault, when?

19:57.196 --> 19:58.829
- This afternoon.

19:58.831 --> 20:00.264
- You must have
the wrong person

20:00.266 --> 20:02.099
because this young man
has been here all afternoon.

20:02.101 --> 20:03.467
- Yes.
- Right.

20:03.469 --> 20:04.969
- Put your hands behind
your back.

20:04.971 --> 20:06.604
- [all protesting]

20:10.843 --> 20:12.777
- Back up.
Back up.

20:15.181 --> 20:17.748
- Back up.
Back up.

20:17.750 --> 20:19.584
Put your hands behind
your back, sir.

20:19.586 --> 20:25.389
- [all protesting]

20:25.391 --> 20:27.892
- Don't resist, Lindor.
Don't resist.

20:27.894 --> 20:29.894
- I didn't even do
nothing, bruh.

20:29.896 --> 20:31.262
I didn't do nothing.

20:31.264 --> 20:33.598
I didn't do nothing.

20:33.600 --> 20:36.033
Come on, Jeremy.
- I'm tired, I'm tired of this.

20:36.035 --> 20:37.902
- Baby, stop.
Okay, we can get him.

20:37.904 --> 20:40.371
- You don't have to do this.
- You don't have to

20:40.373 --> 20:42.373
treat him like this.
- LINDOR: I didn't do

20:42.375 --> 20:43.841
nothing, bruh.
- CORA: Don't resist, baby.

20:43.843 --> 20:45.943
- I didn't do nothing, man.
- OFFICER: Be quiet.

20:45.945 --> 20:47.244
- Come on, bruh.
- JEREMY: No man,

20:47.246 --> 20:48.713
this ain't right.

